caption: Artistic fountains or left over scaffolding? If not for the running water, I would opt for the latter. I know that fountain water is supposed to be drinkable in Paris but not sure where these pipes originate, so I'll give these a miss thankyou.

At the bottom of the fields, these six fountains frame the crossroads with Avenue Montaigne. These are large metal structures releasing water and rotating on themselves. A good concept but I don't find them very aesthetic.
